# glaid Brand Design Guidelines

## Brand Identity
- **Name:** glaid
- **Logo Style:** Modern, minimalist wordmark with circular icon
- **Brand Voice:** Professional, tech-forward, innovative

## Color Palette
### Primary
- **Orange/Coral:** #FF6B4A (Primary accent, CTAs, active states)
- **Dark Gray:** #2D2D2D (Logo background, text)
- **White:** #FFFFFF (Backgrounds, cards)

### Secondary
- **Light Gray:** #F5F5F5 (Subtle backgrounds)
- **Light Coral:** #FFB8A8 (Charts, gradients)

### Semantic
- **Success:** #10B981 (Positive indicators)
- **Warning:** #EF4444 (Negative indicators)
- **Info:** #3B82F6 (Informational)

## Typography
- **Font Family:** Inter, SF Pro Display, -apple-system, system-ui
- **Headings:** Bold (600-700 weight)
- **Body:** Regular (400 weight)
- **Labels:** Medium (500 weight)

## UI Patterns (from Dashboard Inspiration)
- Card-based layouts with subtle shadows
- Orange accent for primary actions
- Clean, generous whitespace
- Rounded corners (8-12px)
- Smooth transitions and micro-animations
- Data visualization with orange/coral tones